rComments: Let me tell you all you need to know about Prof. Clark. Not only is he the sweetest old British man you'll ever meet, who tends to giggle a lot in class, but he genuinely cares about his students. He will do everything in his power to make sure you understand the course material, including give out his home phone number.

Dr Clark is an amazing man who obviously has a passion for what he teaches. However, he as a tendency to downplay everything and rereads everything in class. He also tests you on tedious details that he mentions once and never talks about again. He also seems to think that everyone can cram those details into a midterm or a final.
Such a great prof!  Catch any of his literature courses if you can!!
Clark is the smartest nicest man!

Dr Clark is sincere, helpful, knowledgeable, and funny. Sadly, he often assumes students haven't done the required reading and so reads in class, or will summarize his lecture to that point for someone who has come in late, which can annoy those who have their work done. His passion is myth/lit and if you can get him for Vergil, you are lucky!

Very nice and sincere man. Rather funny when he tells stories of his experiences as an undergrad. However, his expectations are unclear. Often tests you on small things that are briefly mentioned and skips over material that requires multiple classes to discuss. Must be paying attention every second and not miss any classes to do well on exams.
